Gdańsk University of Technology
The Gdańsk University of Technology is a higher education institution that offers a wide range of academic programs, providing services to students, and governing study plans, curriculums, and student activities. It has defined rules for diploma theses, student admissions, academic progress, registration, and reinstatement, as well as specific rules and regulations governing the organization and course of studies for its students. The institution is overseen by a rector, a dean, and a Student Government, which are responsible for the administration and organization of studies.

Dean
The Dean is a high-ranking official responsible for a wide range of academic and administrative matters within a university setting. They oversee various aspects, including student reinstatement and leaves, managing academic programs, overseeing the diploma examination process, determining the schedule for part-time studies, making decisions regarding diploma theses and student registration, and managing student activities, examinations, and academic policies. As the superior of all students at a given faculty, they are responsible for the administration of the faculty and have the authority to make decisions about individual study plans. Additionally, they are responsible for submitting grade changes, validating grades, and handling related administrative tasks. Overall, the Dean plays a crucial role in the academic and administrative structure of the university, ensuring the smooth operation of academic programs and student services.
